WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:03.334
[hissing]
Mm hm.

00:03.404 --> 00:05.237
[hiss]
Mm hm.

00:05.339 --> 00:06.173
Oh!

00:06.874 --> 00:10.608
Antoine believes what
he eats is<i> his</i> business.

00:10.711 --> 00:12.778
Do other predators
feel that way, too?

00:14.081 --> 00:16.315
Would any prey
like to respond?

00:19.120 --> 00:22.587
Muriel? Does it bother you
when Antoine tries to eat you?

00:24.058 --> 00:25.791
Just because you're
on opposite ends

00:25.893 --> 00:27.893
of the food chain doesn't
mean you can't work toge--

00:30.231 --> 00:32.297
It doesn't mean you can't--

00:34.435 --> 00:35.601
Ahem!

00:35.803 --> 00:38.403
It doesn't mean you
can't work togeth--

00:41.375 --> 00:45.510
Oh! I'm sorry, but the
more you distract everyone,

00:45.612 --> 00:47.112
the longer this will take.

00:48.682 --> 00:52.084
I AM listening to you, but if
you really want to be heard,

00:52.186 --> 00:54.319
you should join our
Predator-Prey-Support Group.

00:54.521 --> 00:56.689
Then you could talk
to everyone here.

00:57.291 --> 00:59.325
You could teach all
these hungry predators

00:59.427 --> 01:02.027
the delights of a
carrot-based cuisine.

01:03.697 --> 01:04.730
Sorry, everyone.

01:04.832 --> 01:08.133
I think <i>somebunny</i> just
wants a little attention.

01:08.635 --> 01:11.470
Now, since we all
need to get along,

01:11.572 --> 01:14.606
what if all Predators promised
to only eat vegetables

01:14.708 --> 01:16.341
while staying at
the Sanctuary?

01:21.182 --> 01:23.949
Oh, Sandra.
You can do it!

01:30.290 --> 01:31.189
♪♪

01:31.291 --> 01:33.658
[gasp] Angel! Sandra! Wait!

01:44.305 --> 01:48.373
Hm. It might look like chaos,
but Fluttershy makes it work,

01:48.475 --> 01:50.910
even <i>with</i> Angel running around.

01:51.912 --> 01:55.514
<i> Oooh. Perhaps I can help</i>
<i> those two get along,</i>

01:55.616 --> 01:58.984
<i> before something here</i>
<i> can go terribly wrong.</i>

02:38.059 --> 02:41.625
♪♪

02:41.796 --> 02:44.730
Zecora found this little guy
and brought him to my office,

02:44.832 --> 02:47.499
but I thought he might do
better at the sanctuary.

02:47.601 --> 02:50.068
♪♪

02:51.906 --> 02:54.807
<i>Bringing him here seemed</i>
<i>the right thing to do.</i>

02:54.909 --> 02:58.777
<i>I've never seen geckos breathe</i>
<i>smoke, though, have you?</i>

02:58.979 --> 03:01.280
Oh! I certainly haven't!

03:01.682 --> 03:03.782
I thought we could take
a look at his diet,

03:03.884 --> 03:05.184
plus it's about
time for me

03:05.286 --> 03:07.385
to give all the animals
here a check up.

03:08.155 --> 03:10.155
That's a wonderful idea.

03:15.896 --> 03:18.330
If we really want to
know what's going on,

03:18.432 --> 03:21.233
we need to make sure the
problem isn't your food.

03:25.573 --> 03:27.039
I wouldn't worry too much.

03:27.141 --> 03:29.408
It's probably just
something he's been eating.

03:29.510 --> 03:33.713
Oh, um! Is there anything
else we can do for you?

03:34.115 --> 03:37.316
<i> Ahh! Seeing what</i>
<i> you two do,</i>

03:37.418 --> 03:40.852
<i> the real question</i>
<i> is: "Can I help YOU?"</i>

03:43.157 --> 03:45.691
You mean... me and Angel?

03:45.793 --> 03:46.892
<i>Mm hm.</i>

03:47.394 --> 03:50.295
Oh, he's fine!
We're fine... I-

03:50.397 --> 03:53.132
I just don't always have
time to indulge him.

03:53.634 --> 03:55.901
But we're best friends.

03:56.403 --> 03:59.671
<i>Even the best of friends</i>
<i>need help from time to time.</i>

03:59.773 --> 04:03.343
<i>Come visit me in my hut,</i>
<i>should you change your mind.</i>

04:04.245 --> 04:07.246
OK, thanks! But Angel
and I are great!

04:07.548 --> 04:09.448
Ah! Goodness,
Fluttershy!

04:09.750 --> 04:12.484
Is this the list of
what you do every day!?

04:12.786 --> 04:15.454
How do you find time
for anything else?

04:15.556 --> 04:19.858
Between here and teaching at
the school, I'm not sure I do.

04:24.098 --> 04:26.731
You're going to love
it here, little gecko.

04:28.202 --> 04:30.535
What is it? Not
fluffy enough?

04:32.206 --> 04:33.772
Oh, I'm sorry.

04:33.874 --> 04:36.841
We need to see if your
food is causing your issue.

04:40.347 --> 04:41.179
Huh?!

04:43.250 --> 04:45.684
Mm. Not now, Angel.

04:48.189 --> 04:50.355
They're snake treats
made to look like

04:50.457 --> 04:52.457
chocolate chip cookies!

04:56.830 --> 04:57.763
They're vegan!

04:57.865 --> 04:59.698
Pinkie Pie made a
whole jar of them.

04:59.800 --> 05:02.268
They're all yours
if you promise....

05:02.670 --> 05:05.804
No more trying to eat
Muriel the Baby Elephant.

05:05.928 --> 05:11.528
♪♪

05:12.112 --> 05:12.678
Ah!

05:13.847 --> 05:16.481
No, Angel. I have
too much to do.

05:21.155 --> 05:24.823
Oh! Careful, girl. That neck
is still pretty sore.

05:25.793 --> 05:27.959
Don't forget to shift
your weight, Scout.

05:30.163 --> 05:31.697
What does she want?

05:32.599 --> 05:35.667
Her neck is feeling better,
but a massage every day

05:35.769 --> 05:38.905
for the next week wouldn't
hurt. I'll add it to my list.

05:39.907 --> 05:43.642
Heh. Fluttershy, I've said it
before, but I'll say it again.

05:43.744 --> 05:47.212
This place would be
a <i>zoo</i> without you!

05:50.751 --> 05:51.750
Angel!?

05:53.420 --> 05:55.387
"Listen to you for once?"

05:55.489 --> 05:58.457
Just WHAT exactly is
that supposed to mean!?

06:00.928 --> 06:05.664
Come back! I meant
tell me, not... oh!

06:06.066 --> 06:07.366
Well, whatever it is,

06:07.468 --> 06:09.701
you're the only one
he can tell about it.

06:09.803 --> 06:12.538
Li'l fella just wants
you all to himself.

06:12.740 --> 06:15.474
Unfortunately,
that's not an option.

06:15.576 --> 06:18.609
Aw, he's not causing
any real trouble..

06:18.711 --> 06:20.077
[crash]
Ah!
[birds squawk]

06:20.114 --> 06:21.546
Other than that, possibly.

06:21.648 --> 06:22.514
[crash]
[elephant trumpets]

06:22.616 --> 06:24.583
Or that. I'll just
stop talking.

06:24.985 --> 06:27.886
[groan] I'll take care of it.

06:31.025 --> 06:33.225
I hope this is
important, Angel.

06:33.327 --> 06:36.161
I've barely made a dent in
my to-do list for today.

06:38.369 --> 06:43.369
♪♪

06:43.470 --> 06:45.605
Concentrated
Carrot Extract?

06:46.507 --> 06:49.174
That's for reviving
energy-sapped herbivores.

06:49.276 --> 06:50.842
Are you feeling run down?

06:52.346 --> 06:55.647
You just like the
taste!? Ah! Angel!

06:55.749 --> 06:57.816
That extract is
in short supply!

06:57.918 --> 07:00.552
What's gotten into you?
Every day this week

07:00.654 --> 07:03.155
you've been causing trouble
when I have work to do!

07:05.026 --> 07:07.926
<i>Of course</i> I know you
can't talk to anypony else.

07:08.028 --> 07:11.996
But that's not MY fault.
I have responsibilities!

07:16.537 --> 07:19.137
You're right. We
can't go on like this.

07:19.239 --> 07:21.940
I guess we do need to
see Zecora for help.

07:23.610 --> 07:25.977
<i> No need to sit</i>
<i> and silently stew.</i>

07:26.179 --> 07:28.080
<i> Tell each other</i>
<i> what's bothering you.</i>

07:28.682 --> 07:32.951
He's so impatient, even when
he knows I have work to do.

07:34.655 --> 07:37.622
Well, that's not true!
We talk all the time.

07:38.859 --> 07:41.026
Of course talking at
the Sanctuary counts;

07:41.128 --> 07:43.695
that's where I am when I
don't have a class to teach.

07:44.865 --> 07:47.232
What do you mean,
that's the problem!?

07:48.902 --> 07:50.836
You feel like I'm the
only pony you can talk to

07:50.938 --> 07:52.637
and all I do is ignore you.

07:52.739 --> 07:54.573
Well, <i>I</i> feel like
you don't care

07:54.675 --> 07:56.408
about my responsibilities!

07:58.546 --> 08:03.215
Heh.. Um, as you can see, we're
kind of at an impasse.

08:03.717 --> 08:07.085
<i> Ahh, such luck your</i>
<i> coming here, indeed.</i>

08:07.187 --> 08:09.821
<i> Behold, the antidote</i>
<i> you need.</i>

08:10.123 --> 08:13.625
Is... this what you
meant by "help us"?

08:13.727 --> 08:16.228
<i> When trouble brews</i>
<i> between you two,</i>

08:16.330 --> 08:18.063
<i> turning sister</i>
<i> against brother.</i>

08:18.165 --> 08:20.766
<i> True understanding</i>
<i> is what's due,</i>

08:20.868 --> 08:23.002
<i> each must come to</i>
<i> know the other.</i>

08:23.904 --> 08:27.172
<i> There's no time to</i>
<i> waste, go directly home,</i>

08:27.274 --> 08:30.809
<i> but you both must taste</i>
<i> when you're finally alone.</i>

08:32.613 --> 08:34.813
♪♪

08:34.915 --> 08:36.515
Not yet, Angel.

08:36.617 --> 08:39.551
Zecora told us to take it
together when we got home.

08:39.675 --> 08:44.075
♪♪

08:44.258 --> 08:47.259
Oh! I suppose we could dust
off the ol' picnic blanket.

08:47.361 --> 08:49.229
It'll be just
like old times.

08:50.231 --> 08:51.897
We'll drink the
potion and settle in

08:51.999 --> 08:53.799
for a nice tea party.

08:53.901 --> 08:56.435
I can barely remember
the last time we did that!|

08:56.537 --> 08:58.971
I've been so busy
at the Sanctuary...

08:59.373 --> 09:02.207
Though.. I really need to keep
an eye on Zecora's gecko

09:02.309 --> 09:04.843
and I haven't finished
any of today's chores...

09:05.145 --> 09:08.013
If I don't, the animals won't
get the care they need!

09:08.115 --> 09:10.615
Oh. Maybe we should save
the potion until aft--

09:10.717 --> 09:13.518
Angel! Zecora said
to go home first!

09:18.125 --> 09:20.792
I <i>know</i> she said we have
to take it together so...

09:20.894 --> 09:22.360
I guess I have to now.

09:25.732 --> 09:29.135
I wonder what it's
going to dooWHOOOAA.-

09:30.337 --> 09:35.239
Whoa whoa whoa! Hang on, hold
up, am I a pony!? Why am I a pony!?

09:37.010 --> 09:38.276
Eeeeek!

09:41.359 --> 09:43.859
<i>♪ [dramatic sting] ♪</i>

09:44.184 --> 09:46.618
Question: did we
switch bodies?

09:46.720 --> 09:52.524
♪♪

09:53.326 --> 09:55.493
Whoa! Whoa!

09:57.965 --> 10:01.032
Seriously, I'm a
pony? La la la la!

10:01.134 --> 10:02.301
Talking is so cool!

10:02.403 --> 10:04.369
Do you think this was what
Zecora meant to happen?

10:06.373 --> 10:09.641
How are you gonna do
your <i>chores</i>!? Really?

10:09.743 --> 10:11.343
<i>That's</i> what you're
worried about?

10:13.614 --> 10:15.714
Pff. Well, maybe I don't
WANNA switch back!

10:15.816 --> 10:17.783
I've only been able to
talk to YOU since we met,

10:17.885 --> 10:20.285
and now I can talk
to anypony I want!

10:23.590 --> 10:24.956
Roses are red,
violets are blue,

10:25.058 --> 10:26.825
you sell flowers
and so do you!

10:27.227 --> 10:29.561
Rubber baby buggy bumpers!
Rubber baby buggy bumpers!

10:30.597 --> 10:32.964
Toy boat! Toy boat!
Toy boa-AH!

10:33.667 --> 10:34.699
Oh, come on!

10:36.603 --> 10:40.104
I am so too listening! Quit
bein' so bossy because -- Ah!

10:41.341 --> 10:42.341
Are there carrots around here!?

10:46.447 --> 10:48.713
You think Zecora gave
us the wrong potion,

10:48.815 --> 10:50.649
so you're gonna go to
her hut in the forest

10:50.751 --> 10:52.251
and get something
to switch us back.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.153
All by yourself?

10:54.255 --> 10:56.922
You REALLY don't know what
it's like being a bunny.

10:57.824 --> 11:00.692
Good luck with <i>that</i>. I'm
gonna go find those carrots.

11:02.629 --> 11:05.897
"I need to finish your
chores?" Ha, ha, ha!

11:06.099 --> 11:07.332
I don't work for you!

11:07.434 --> 11:10.135
And caring about other
animals is a <i>you</i> thing.

11:10.436 --> 11:11.447
<i> ♪ [horror sting] ♪</i>

11:12.706 --> 11:15.174
The <i>stare</i>!? You
can still do that?

11:15.376 --> 11:18.710
Ugh! No fair making me do your
bidding against my will!

11:18.812 --> 11:24.349
<i> ♪ [horror film music] ♪</i>

11:24.451 --> 11:27.052
All right! I'll go
do your lame chores

11:27.154 --> 11:28.753
while you go see Zecora.

11:32.739 --> 11:37.239
♪♪

11:37.364 --> 11:39.197
Anypony know where
that useless list

11:39.299 --> 11:41.467
of Fluttershy's chores is?

11:42.269 --> 11:43.702
Dr. Fauna: Hey, Fluttershy.

11:43.804 --> 11:46.037
I was starting to wonder
if you'd make it back.

11:46.239 --> 11:48.607
Fluttershy! Oh,
yeah! Uh, that's me!

11:48.709 --> 11:50.976
Definitely Fluttershy,
a hundred percent.

11:52.813 --> 11:53.779
Oh...kay.

11:53.881 --> 11:57.016
See how.. <i>shy</i> I am?

11:58.018 --> 11:59.150
I talk to animals...

11:59.252 --> 12:01.052
I want to
marry Discord...

12:01.154 --> 12:02.855
Your list is
over there.

12:03.657 --> 12:05.857
Oh. Yeah. There's my
good ol' list of chores

12:05.959 --> 12:07.793
that I will absolutely
NOT rush through

12:07.895 --> 12:10.829
because I definitely do not
have better things to do.

12:13.900 --> 12:16.034
Well, well, well.

12:16.236 --> 12:18.169
Remember <i>me</i>?

12:18.606 --> 12:22.207
Ohh. I hope the gem tart stall
is still there again.

12:22.409 --> 12:23.975
I could use a snack.

12:24.177 --> 12:26.745
You nearly bought every tart
they had last time, Spike.

12:26.847 --> 12:28.313
I can't imagine they
wouldn't show up

12:28.415 --> 12:29.983
when there's a great
customer like you.

12:31.585 --> 12:33.752
Oh. Hi, Angel.
What's going on?

12:37.991 --> 12:39.459
Do you know what
he's trying to say?

12:39.783 --> 12:40.360
Nope.

12:40.461 --> 12:43.194
Sorry, Angel. You should
probably find Fluttershy.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.330
If I see her, I'll let her
know you're looking for her.

12:45.432 --> 12:53.400
♪♪

13:02.583 --> 13:04.849
AND we're gonna keep
at it until you start

13:04.951 --> 13:06.685
to develop a
taste for it.

13:09.322 --> 13:11.389
Uh, check Muriel's trunk...

13:18.965 --> 13:20.331
Ah, seems fine to me.

13:20.433 --> 13:22.000
As long as we don't
need those keys..

13:23.170 --> 13:26.471
Anyway. Let's see. Massage
Clementine's neck...

13:32.412 --> 13:34.279
Get Scout to switch legs?

13:36.149 --> 13:37.683
Eh. Probably best not to wake him.

13:37.785 --> 13:39.784
Did the thing with the
thing, yada, yada, yada,

13:39.886 --> 13:40.986
animals, animals, animals.

13:41.088 --> 13:45.256
All that's left is.. monitor
Zecora's gecko until bedtime!?

13:49.596 --> 13:52.330
All right, dude. How
about we do bedtime now?

13:54.201 --> 13:56.034
Yeah, eating makes
me tired too.

13:56.236 --> 13:59.037
Which reminds me, there's
some carrot extract

13:59.139 --> 14:00.672
with my name on it.

14:01.975 --> 14:04.209
OK! Let's get you fed
and off to dreamland.

14:04.411 --> 14:05.543
What do you eat, anyway?

14:07.414 --> 14:09.381
Whaddya say, Snake? Can you
find something else to eat

14:09.483 --> 14:11.316
if I borrow those cookies
for my friend here?

14:11.618 --> 14:14.953
♪♪

14:19.759 --> 14:21.393
I'm sure
that's normal.

14:21.795 --> 14:23.395
There you go.
Problem solved.

14:23.597 --> 14:25.598
I don't see what's so
hard about this job.

14:26.900 --> 14:29.400
Fluttershy is
SUCH a whiner!

14:29.502 --> 14:50.470
♪♪

14:52.125 --> 14:53.491
♪♪

14:59.766 --> 15:04.569
♪♪

15:04.671 --> 15:07.072
<i> Quite a day, my fuzzy friend!</i>

15:07.174 --> 15:09.541
<i> Did things work out</i>
<i> for you in the end?</i>

15:12.045 --> 15:16.481
<i> I'm sorry, dear bunny,</i>
<i> that things seem so grave,</i>

15:16.583 --> 15:19.452
<i> but I don't understand</i>
<i> when you sign and wave.</i>

15:20.754 --> 15:25.621
<i>A single link to all the world.</i>
<i> only one in all the land.</i>

15:26.123 --> 15:30.157
<i> How special she must be to</i>
<i> you, the one who understands.</i>

15:31.259 --> 15:33.029
<i> Perhaps if you explained</i>
<i> what you wanted</i>

15:33.131 --> 15:34.899
<i> to somepony who understood,</i>

15:35.001 --> 15:36.935
<i> if you truly felt</i>
<i> heard and valued,</i>

15:37.037 --> 15:39.005
<i> all would return to good.</i>

15:40.207 --> 15:43.241
<i> And if you were</i>
<i> to both apologize,</i>

15:43.343 --> 15:45.076
<i> having learned</i>
<i> this little lesson,</i>

15:45.378 --> 15:47.479
<i> I imagine that</i>
<i> might bring an end</i>

15:47.581 --> 15:49.647
<i> to the friendship</i>
<i> therapy session.</i>

15:49.771 --> 15:54.171
♪♪

15:58.124 --> 15:58.990
Dr. Fauna: Fluttershy?

15:59.092 --> 16:01.827
Do you mind helping me look
for Muriel the Baby Elephant?

16:02.329 --> 16:04.329
Oh, she's having
dinner with Antoine.

16:04.631 --> 16:06.364
Antoine the PYTHON!?

16:06.666 --> 16:07.832
It was on the list:

16:07.934 --> 16:11.370
"Remember Antoine wants to
have Muriel over for dinner."

16:11.972 --> 16:16.608
Not<i> over</i> for dinner! He
wants to have her FOR DINNER!

16:17.110 --> 16:18.576
Wait. WHAT!?

16:22.295 --> 16:26.595
♪♪

16:26.720 --> 16:31.056
Bad snake! Open your mouth
this instant, Mister!

16:36.229 --> 16:42.867
<i> ♪ [tense music] ♪</i>

16:44.971 --> 16:48.172
What is going on!? You did
all the chores on your list.

16:48.274 --> 16:49.274
Huh!? Didn't you!?

16:49.776 --> 16:52.110
Well, technically,
I did'em, kind of.

16:52.212 --> 16:54.879
But more technically,
it's not <i>my</i> list.

16:55.181 --> 16:56.114
You wrote it!

16:56.216 --> 16:57.215
Did I, though?

16:57.517 --> 16:59.618
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU!?

17:00.220 --> 17:02.520
You do NOT wanna know.

17:05.926 --> 17:07.025
Huh?

17:10.330 --> 17:11.129
Angel?

17:11.231 --> 17:12.830
What's wrong
with her... him?

17:12.932 --> 17:13.833
What happened!?

17:14.735 --> 17:16.234
He's exhausted!

17:18.038 --> 17:19.237
Fluttershy, I need a jar

17:19.339 --> 17:21.740
of concentrated
carrot extract, STAT!

17:21.842 --> 17:24.175
Ah! It's locked in
the supply room.

17:24.477 --> 17:25.677
Where are your keys!?

17:27.279 --> 17:28.379
Uh....

17:29.750 --> 17:31.783
Any ideas how to get the
keys out of the elephant

17:31.885 --> 17:33.318
that's inside the snake?

17:35.688 --> 17:39.090
OK! Point taken. And
I totally deserve it.

17:39.292 --> 17:41.760
I did not provide you with the
care that Fluttershy would.

17:42.362 --> 17:43.928
But NOW you know
what it's like

17:44.030 --> 17:45.330
not to get the
level of attention

17:45.432 --> 17:46.965
to which you've
become accustomed!

17:49.369 --> 17:52.570
The point is Fluttershy is
trapped in my bunny body

17:52.672 --> 17:54.539
and if we don't help
her, maybe none of us

17:54.641 --> 17:57.642
will get her attention. I get
that you don't want to help <i>me</i>,

17:57.744 --> 17:59.544
but don't you want to help <i>her</i>?

18:03.483 --> 18:06.484
<i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

18:06.586 --> 18:14.354
♪♪

18:14.494 --> 18:15.760
Here goes nothing.

18:16.162 --> 18:18.530
♪♪

18:28.241 --> 18:30.441
Now we just need to get
those keys out of there..

18:37.117 --> 18:39.217
Ha, ha! Nice
one, snake.

18:41.421 --> 18:42.854
I guess Fluttershy was right.

18:43.156 --> 18:45.123
Predators and prey
<i>can</i> work together.

18:45.225 --> 18:50.761
♪♪

18:53.233 --> 18:56.568
This place is so. Much. Work!

18:57.070 --> 19:01.239
Oh! I know. I have no clue
how you do it all,

19:01.341 --> 19:02.740
but we are so grateful.

19:02.842 --> 19:08.313
♪♪

19:08.415 --> 19:11.349
I can't believe she
does this every day!

19:11.451 --> 19:14.052
I just wish I could
tell her myself..

19:14.154 --> 19:14.820
What?

19:15.122 --> 19:20.025
♪♪

19:22.028 --> 19:25.063
♪♪

19:25.165 --> 19:26.065
You're awake!

19:27.367 --> 19:29.300
"It was so hard getting
to Zecora's hut?

19:29.402 --> 19:30.535
And impossible getting back?

19:30.637 --> 19:32.537
You can't believe I
survive like this?"

19:34.674 --> 19:37.208
Well, I can't believe
<i>you</i> work here every day!

19:37.310 --> 19:39.243
These animals are crazy!

19:39.345 --> 19:41.347
No wonder you don't
have time for me!

19:42.849 --> 19:45.784
My life is hard? No,
YOUR life is hard!

19:46.286 --> 19:50.621
You never appreciated me?
No, I never appreciated <i>you</i>!

19:53.059 --> 19:56.294
You're sorry? I'm sorry too!!

19:56.596 --> 20:00.530
Come here, you little bunny
who's a pony who's a bunny! Ooo!

20:06.906 --> 20:10.875
Oh, my goodness! I'm
back! I'm a pony again!

20:14.514 --> 20:19.150
Oh, Angel, I promise to always
make time for you from now on.

20:20.820 --> 20:25.424
What do you mean maybe I won't
have to? You want to do.. WHAT?

20:26.426 --> 20:27.992
...and that's when I realized

20:28.094 --> 20:30.595
Fluttershy doesn't have to
be the only one I talk to.

20:30.997 --> 20:33.466
I can come here and
talk to all of you.

20:34.868 --> 20:37.468
And now that I know how much
work goes into this place,

20:37.670 --> 20:41.072
I suppose I could kinda, sorta
help out every now and then.

20:45.512 --> 20:48.613
Oh, Angel! That is so sweet,

20:48.715 --> 20:51.149
but now that I know what
you go through every day,

20:51.251 --> 20:54.419
I understand why your time
with me is so important.

20:54.621 --> 20:57.688
I promise to always
make time for you!

21:04.531 --> 21:07.065
Turns out your friend, here,
doesn't have a problem at all.

21:07.167 --> 21:10.100
He isn't a gecko.
He's a fire lizard!

21:11.471 --> 21:13.638
I forgot that before
they get their flame,

21:13.740 --> 21:15.307
it's hard to
tell them apart.

21:16.309 --> 21:19.510
<i> I'm glad to discover where</i>
<i> the source of it lies,</i>

21:19.712 --> 21:23.915
<i> or the fire that he breathes</i>
<i> would be quite the surprise.</i>

21:24.017 --> 21:26.217
Speaking of surprises...

21:26.619 --> 21:29.187
Can you please
<i>never</i> do that again?

21:29.311 --> 21:32.911
♪♪
